Barn: Birgitta f. 41, Jan 43, Sigfrid 47. — Stud:ex. i Kalmar 29, teok fil ex. i Lund 31, teol. kand. 35 prakt. teol. prov samt prästvigd för Växjö stift 36. Aisisist. v. ’SV. ’sjöimianisikyrkan i Roitfter-daim 33-34, tjg. s. v. koimmiiin. i Bya-r;uim, Kalmar, Lekaryd-Härdiöv stam t Lianiniackeide, s. piast :adj. i Runsten o. t’f. kyrkoaidj. i Almiundisryd, kommin. i S Sigfrid ,sed. 43.
translated: Madestam, Ernst Enok Johannes, vicar, married to Edsia Ljungdahl, born on January 23, 1910 in Made sjö, Kalmar. Children: Birgitta, born in 1941, Jan in 1943, Sigfrid in 1947. — Studied: completed secondary education in Kalmar in 1929, obtained a Bachelor's degree in theology from Lund in 1931, completed theological studies and practical theological examination, ordained as a priest for the Växjö diocese in 1936. Assisting vicar at the Swedish Mission Church in Roitfter-daim from 1933-34, served as vicar in Bya-r;uim, Kalmar, Lekaryd-Härdiöv stam in Lianiniackeide, assistant adjutant in Runsten and churchwarden in Almiundisryd, vicar in S Sigfrid since 1943.
